{"comments":"WetMedia Types — ADTs for wet paint simulation.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nWet media simulation enables natural media behaviors in digital painting.\nDifferent media types (watercolor, oil, acrylic) have distinct properties\nfor wetness, flow, and interaction with the canvas.\n\n## Media Types\n\n- **Watercolor**: Transparent, flows, pools at edges\n- **OilPaint**: Thick, blends, supports impasto\n- **Acrylic**: Quick-drying, versatile coverage\n- **Gouache**: Opaque watercolor behavior\n- **Ink**: Fluid, bleeds at edges\n- **WetIntoWet**: Painting into existing wet areas\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[82,15],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/WetMedia/Types.purs","start":[82,3]},"title":"Watercolor"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[83,13],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/WetMedia/Types.purs","start":[83,3]},"title":"OilPaint"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[84,12],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/WetMedia/Types.purs","start":[84,3]},"title":"Acrylic"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[85,12],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/WetMedia/Types.purs","start":[85,3]},"title":"Gouache"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[86,8],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/WetMedia/Types.purs","start":[86,3]},"title":"Ink"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[87,15],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/WetMedia/Types.purs","start":[87,3]},"title":"WetIntoWet"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"conte